description:
Come stay in a beautifully renovated, large apartment in the heart of Harlem. Located right near Central Park, only 5 blocks away! Walking distance to Morningside Park and Columbia University, St Johns Cathedral, farmers markets and more. Plenty of restaurants, bars, museums, beer gardens. Major subway lines, two blocks away and only 15 minutes to Time Square or Rockefeller Center. (Great for holiday season). 

My place is good for couples, solo adventurers, and business travelers.

We have a very spacious apartment on the 3rd floor. Large windows in both the living and dining room offer tons of natural sunlight. Newly renovated, large kitchen and dining room. Comfortable living room with a smart tv.

You will have access to the whole apartment except for one bedroom which we are using for storage.

We are happy to help make recommendations, assist with directions etc. Please let us know right away if there are any issues.

Harlem is a lively neighborhood, with plenty of restaurants, bars, pubs, churches and parks. There is plenty of  culture, charm and diversity to keep you interested and entertained.  You are also in close proximity to everything NYC has to offer.

Yes. The 2/3 train is a block away (express trains) and the b/c is a block away in the other direction. 
There are major bus lines, the m7 of which takes you downtown to the west village and the m2 which takes you to the east side. There are also citibikes right near our place on 110th street.

We will provide bedding, towels, and cooking supplies/utensils for your use. There is also access to a large smart TV and wireless internet.  Anything else you might need, please feel free to inquire.

hosts.about: I am a 34 year old, professional in the field of education. I received my doctorate from Teachers College, Columbia University. I have lived in NYC for the last 16 years and can share information about the neighborhoods, best dinner/bar stops. I enjoy running, reading, dining out, and spending time with my family and friends. I have been fortunate enough to travel to some wonderful places, but I'm excited at the possibility of more travel with my husband. We were just married in December of 2015, and look forward to touring through more of Europe, taking in museums, plazas, good food and culture! I am a responsible, respectful and reliable person.

Next time we visit New York Cristina will be the first we call !
